ns"}],"verses":[{"id":"rec8X8Gj7XcaOloMs","ref":"Ps.77.1","text":"I cried unto God with my voice, even unto God with my voice; and he gave ear unto me."},{"id":"recSgBUpyIwnwarkw","ref":"Ps.77.2","text":"In the day of my trouble I sought the Lord: my sore ran in the night, and ceased not: my soul refused to be comforted."},{"id":"rec588cO9rIPipNTv","ref":"Ps.77.3","text":"I remembered God, and was troubled: I complained, and my spirit was overwhelmed. Selah."},{"id":"rec73rUYQPpfje8NM","ref":"Ps.77.4","text":"Thou holdest mine eyes waking: I am so troubled that I cannot speak."},{"id":"rec98u0gzcruyxk04","ref":"Ps.77.5","text":"I have considered the days of old, the years of ancient times."},{"id":"recFnwjmMm8vKTb8m","ref":"Ps.77.6","text":"I call to remembrance my song in the night: I commune with mine own heart: and my spirit made diligent search."},{"id":"recqGjrVruzVvTJZ2","ref":"Ps.77.7","text":"Will the Lord cast off for ever? and will he be favourable no more?"},{"id":"rec21ficor5zw5r04","ref":"Ps.77.8","text":"Is his mercy clean gone for ever? doth his promise fail for evermore?"}]}
